{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9971c615-bd72-41c5-a138-57c22f6b80a8","content":"Run this:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis uses `dotnet watch` for hot reload and `--filter` to match only that test by name. Every time you save a file, it will re-run just that single test.\n\nYou can also use the shorter display name filter:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\n`Name=` does an exact match on the test method name, while `FullyQualifiedName~` does a substring/contains match including the namespace and class.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8293c403-5926-4f82-b1bf-4eb48c54340f","outputTokens":157,"requestId":"0BC6:1A4FD7:74E5ED:8791F6:69F011F0"},"id":"bf9ff620-ef64-4179-aa8f-9b44a18d2098","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:48:38.770Z","parentId":"bcf6cb19-4379-43d7-8317-5171f3f01910"}
